title: hand_warmer
body:
A device that generates heat and is used to keep the hands warm.  These devices can be disposable or reusable and they produce heat through various means, such as chemical reaction, burning fuel, or using electricity.

Disposable hand warmers are a simple sealed pouch filled with material that undergoes a chemical reaction that produces heat.  Reusable hand warmers commonly produce heat either through the combustion of a fuel, as is the case with charcoal or lighter fluid hand warmers, or using electricity through a heating coil, as is the case for battery hand warmers.

A device similar to a disposable hand warmer that has been designed to adhere to the bottom of a sock is referred to as a [[toe warmer]].

title: lounge_chair
body:
A type of outdoor furniture that allows a sunbather to [[reclining|recline]] in a relaxed position. Often found at a [[beach]] or at [[poolside]], possibly in conjunction with a [[parasol]]. Also known as a sun lounger, chaise lounge (US), or deck chair (UK).

They serve a similar purpose as a deck chair, though a deck chair is a type of folding chair (with a fabric or vinyl strip that forms the seat and backrest, e.g. post #1159067) and the shapes are reversed. A sun lounger has a longer seat than back, while a deck chair has a longer back than seat.

title: karate
body:
[b]Karate[/b] (空手) is a [[martial arts|martial art]] developed in the Ryukyu Kingdom. It developed from the indigenous Ryukyuan martial arts (called [i]te[/i] (手), "hand"; [i]tii[/i] in Okinawan) under the influence of [[china|Chinese]] martial arts, particularly Fujian White Crane. Karate is now predominantly a striking art using punching, kicking, knee strikes, elbow strikes and open-hand techniques such as knife-hands, spear-hands, and palm-heel strikes. Historically, and in some modern styles, grappling, throws, joint locks, restraints, and vital-point strikes are also taught. A karate practitioner is called a [i]karateka[/i] (空手家).

title: north_carolina_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the battleship USS [i]North Carolina[/i] (BB-55).
Character design by [[Kishiyo]], voiced by [[Horie Yui]].

h4. Appearance
North Carolina is portrayed in the fairly typical fashion for Americans, being [[blonde_hair|blonde-haired]], [[blue_eyes|blue-eyed]], tall, and having [[large breasts]]. She wears a stylized US Navy dress uniform and brandishes her namesake state's flag on her right shoulder as an [[armband]].

h4. Personality
Personality-wise, North Carolina will admit to having none whatsoever, though she generally behaves in a courteous and professional manner. However, as her affection level rises (and when she's Pledged to), she'll reveal a hidden lewd side, inquiring as to any possible interest in [[playboy bunny|bunnysuits]]. As a result, she is frequently portrayed wearing them in fanart and eventually received [[north_carolina_(the_heart's_desire)_(azur_lane)|an official costume]] after overwhelming fan demand.

h4. History
[i]North Carolina[/i] was the first new battleship to be built after the signing of the Washington and London naval treaties, in response to Imperial Japan's new battleship construction in violation of the agreements. Her experience during World War II was limited mostly to shore bombardment and anti-aircraft operations, save for an incident in which she and two other ships were torpedoed by the Japanese submarine [[I-19 (Azur Lane)|]]. In the 1960s, she was converted into a museum ship and can be visited today in Wilmington, North Carolina.

She tries to be mature by bringing her version of a hot drink to an onsen, but finds the cola to be disgusting due to it having gone flat. She is friends with Chinatsu and [[Mary Cochran]]. She wanted to walk with the Producer under an umbrella together and tried to get a taste of [[Mochizuki Hijiri]]’s cake until Hijiri began to cry in worry for a sugar figurine’s life. Yui is quick to point out that [[Ohta Yuu]]’s chocolate figure is suspicious and hopes Akky isn’t in any danger.

title: koutetsu_teikoku
body:
[b]Steel Empire[/b] (originally released as [i]Koutetsu Teikoku[/i] (鋼鉄帝国) in Japan, and otherwise known in various English materials as [b]The Steel Empire[/b] or [b]Empire of Steel[/b]) is a side-scrolling shoot 'em up [[video game]] released on the Sega Genesis / [[Sega Mega Drive]] home consoles in 1992, and was later ported to the Nintendo [[Game Boy Advance]] in 2004 and to the [[Nintendo 3DS]] in 2014.

Steel Empire is notable amongst shoot 'em up games for its unique aesthetic designs. Mostly low-tech in nature, with its being set in the late-19th century of an alternate world, the game's aircraft, weaponry, powerups, environments, enemies and bosses are heavily stylized adding strong [[steampunk]] elements to the style, themes and visuals of the game. Steam power, propeller-based aircraft, biplanes, dirigibles and heavily armored steam trains with giant cannons play large roles in the game's protagonists and opponents.

title: figure_four_leglock
body:
The wrestler stands over the opponent who is lying on the mat face up and grasps a leg of the opponent. The wrestler then does a spinning toe hold and grasps the other leg, crossing them into a "4" (hence the name) as he does so and falls to the mat, applying pressure to the opponent's crossed legs with his own. 

While the hold applies pressure to the knee, it actually can be very painful to the shin of the victim. While the move is primarily a submission move, if the opponent has his shoulders on the mat, the referee can make a three count for a pinfall. If the referee is distracted, heel wrestlers may grab onto the ropes while executing the move to gain leverage and inflict more pain. 

With enough strength and willpower, the wrestler on defense can flip himself (and also their opponent) over onto their belly, which is said to reverse the pressure to the one who initially had the hold locked in.

This is innovated by "Nature Boy" Buddy Rogers and popularized by Ric Flair. Flair's daughter, [[WWE]] superstar [[Charlotte Flair]], uses a bridging variation which she calls the [i]Figure-Eight Leglock[/i].

title: the_batter_(off)
body:
The main character of the game [[off (game)|OFF]]. His skin is entirely [[white_skin|white]], and he wears an old [[baseball uniform]], with a black [[baseball_cap|cap]] sometimes hiding his eyes, and fights with a metallic [[baseball_bat|bat]]. Some character interpretations depict him as having [[extra_eyes|four eyes]]. His hair is not shown, but it's supposed he has black hair.

Is often followed by floating circles, referencing his ingame add-ons and referred to as his "Party", and strongly opposes ghosts. His goal is the purification of the world.

[spoiler]
It's eventually revealed that his "purification" is essentially the end of the world, as every area that he cleansed is left white and empty, with only a few exceptions, leaving demons behind but killing almost all the population.
It's also revealed that he's not human, and it's explained he acts out of free will.
By the end of the game, the player gets the choice to support the Batter in his last fight or to betray him, causing the Batter's appearance to change from an emotionless man to a giant humanoid abomination with a elongated mouth. This form is known as "Bad Batter."
[/spoiler]

Due to his actions, he's sometimes associated with [[chara (undertale)|Chara]] from [i][[Undertale]][/i], even if he has different reasons, seeing his actions as a mercy killing, compared to Chara's sadistic tendencies.

title: orca
body:
The [b]Orca[/b] ([i]Orcinus orca[/i]) is a black and white carnivorous marine mammal. Commonly known as the [b]killer whale[/b] and also known as [b]orca whale[/b]. The orca is the largest species of dolphin, being part of the family Delphinidae. (Delphinidae is within the Odontoceti or toothed whales, which is within the Cetacea or whales, so orcas are whales in the sense that all dolphins are whales.)

Usually growing around 5-8 meters long, orcas are known to be apex predators of the sea, as they have no natural predators.

title: h6k
body:
[b]H6K[/b], or [b]Kawanishi H6K[/b], was a flying boat produced by the Kawanishi Aircraft Company and used during World War II for maritime patrol duties by Imperial Japanese Navy. The Allied reporting name for the type was [b]Mavis[/b]; the Navy designation was "[b]Type 97 Large Flying Boat[/b]" (九七式大型飛行艇).

The aircraft was designed in response to a Navy requirement of 1934 for a long-range flying boat and incorporated knowledge gleaned by a Kawanishi team that visited the Short Brothers factory in the UK.

H6Ks were deployed from 1938 onwards, first seeing service in the Sino-Japanese War and were in widespread use by the time the full-scale Pacific War erupted, in December 1941. At that time of the war, four [i]Kōkūtai[/i] (air groups) operated a total of 66 H6K4s.

The type had some success over South East Asia and the South West Pacific. H6Ks had excellent endurance, being able to undertake 24-hour patrols, and were often used for long-range reconnaissance and bombing missions. From bases in the Dutch East Indies, they were able to undertake missions over a large portion of Australia.

However, the H6K became vulnerable to a newer generation of more heavily armed and faster fighters. It continued in service throughout the war, in areas where the risk of interception was low. In front-line service, it was replaced by the Kawanishi H8K.

title: gankutsuou
body:
巌窟王, lit. [i]The King of the Cave[/i], released as [i]Gankutsuou: The Count of Monte Cristo[/i] in English

A 2004 animated adaptation/re-imagining of Alexandre Dumas's classic french novel, "[i]The Count of Monte Cristo[/i]":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Count_of_Monte_Cristo, by GONZO. The setting is moved to the year 5053 (vs. 1815-1838 in the novel), though the majority of the story remains in France. The protagonist is [[Albert de Morcerf]] instead of Edmond Dantes. 

The series is notable for its use of a "collage" effect where the hair and clothing of characters act as "holes" to stationary backgrounds underneath (the pattern stays still, but the opening changes as the characters move around) (see post #139047 for a good example of the effect on Haydee). The series also makes heavy use of CG art.

A manga by Maeda Mahiro, director of the TV series, was also released, beginning in 2005 in Kodansha's [i]Afternoon[/i].

A type of barren, devastated terrain that is inhospitable to life. title: kimura_lock
body:
Kimura (Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu), chicken wing/double wristlock ([[wrestling]]), or reverse keylock are terms used to specify a medial keylock known in [[judo]] as gyaku ude-garami (reverse arm entanglement) or simply as ude-garami. 

The application is similar to the americana, except that it is reversed. It needs some space behind the opponent to be effective, and can be applied from the side control or guard. Contrary to the americana, the opponent's wrist is grabbed with the hand on the same side, and the opposite arm is put behind the opponent's arm, again grabbing the attacker's wrist and forming a figure-four. By controlling the opponent's body and cranking the arm away from the attacker, pressure is put on the shoulder joint, and depending on the angle, also the elbow joint (in some variations the opponent's arm is brought behind their back, resulting in a finishing position resembling that of the hammerlock).

The kimura was named after the judoka Kimura Masahiko, who used it to defeat one of the founders of Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu, Hélio Gracie. It is then popularized in pro wrestling by [[WWE]] wrestler [[Brock Lesnar]], where he would use it often to break his opponent's arm, in storyline.

Realizing the chaos brought by the outbreak, the two became separated and arrive at the city's police station to seek shelter. The two arrived at the precinct for their own purposes as they find for possible ways to escape the city as the station was also swarmed by the undead.

After the events of Raccoon City, Leon departs and was apprehended by the US military, eventually becoming a STRATCOM agent alongside with a fellow agent, [[Jack Krauser]].

h4.Appearance
Leon is a tall man with [[blonde hair|blonde]] or [[brown hair|brown]] hair in a [[curtained hair|curtained fashion]] and [[blue eyes]]. His appearance varies throughout the series.

* [b]Resident Evil 2[/b]: Leon wears a [[police uniform]] with [[blue shirt]], [[blue pants]], [[elbow pads]], [[fingerless gloves]], and black boots. In the 1998 version, Leon wears a police uniform containing [[shoulder pads]] and a [[body armor]] with the "R.P.D." logo imprinted on it. In the 2019 remake, Leon wears a more modern uniform, now containing numerous [[pouch|pouches]] and a [[knee pads|knee pad]]. The R.P.D.'s  patch is also imprinted on the blue shirt.
* [b]Resident Evil 4[/b]: Leon has a [[brown jacket]] along with a [[black shirt]], [[fingerless gloves]], [[black pants]], and a pair of [[black footwear|black shoes]]. After losing his jacket, a [[holster]] can be seen wrapped around his torso.
* [b]Resident Evil: The Darkside Chronicles[/b]: During the events of Operation: Javier, Leon wears a similar outfit to the ones he wore in [i]Resident Evil 4[/i], albeit he sports a [[green pants]] with a [[camouflage]] pattern and lacks a jacket.
* [b]Resident Evil 6[/b]: Leon has a much more matured appearance in [i]Resident Evil 6[/i], he sports a [[leather jacket|black leather jacket]] along with [[black shirt]], [[white pants]], and black shoes.

He is a childhood acquaintance of [[moritaka (housamo)|Inuzuka Shino Moritaka]] with a rather world-weary disposition. When he works as part of the Invaders, he acts in operations devised by Inumura Daikaku Masanori and is specially charged with infiltrating other guilds and attacking their VIPs. He has a self-sacrificial personality who chooses to do the dirty work himself. Yoshito prefers masters who treat him not as a person with feelings, but as a tool. Here in Tokyo, Yoshito fights with a giant robot body his guildmaster has given him. This robot is able to install the past memories of others. If Yoshito were to use it in conjunction with his Sacred Artifact, he could conceivably copy and recreate the techniques of the other Hakkenshi. He has a very thin attachment to life and strongly believes himself to be replaceable. Yoshito apparently shows sympathy akin to pity when it comes to people who do not have a definite singular sense of self. In contrast, he tends to avoid those with high self-esteem and those who pride themselves as the one true ancestor or originator.

title: pyrrha_nikos
body:
Pyrrha Nikos is a character from [[RWBY]], a Rooster Teeth production. Her design is inspired by Achilles. 

Pyrrha is the "P" in Team JNPR. She is friendly, thoughtful, and self-sacrificing. Nicknamed the "Invincible Girl" by the public for her prodigal skill in student combat tournaments.

[spoiler]
She is killed near the end of volume 3 by Cinder Fall with the remains of her weapons gear and armor recovered and then melted down and incorporated into Jaune Arc's sword and shield and armor in the 6 month time-skip between volume 3 and 4 as a memento of her to him.  
[/spoiler]


h4. Abilities

Pyrrha wields [[milo_and_akouo|Miló]] and [[milo_and_akouo|Akoúo̱]]. Miló is a weapon with three forms: a [[javelin (spear)|]] [[spear]], a [[xiphos_(sword)|xiphos]] (small [[sword]]), or a [[rifle]]. It is red with bronze trimming. Akoúo̱ is a bronze metal rounded [[shield]] often worn as a [[buckler]]. 

Her weapons are also her emblem (a shield and spear). Pyrrha's semblance is "polarity" (control over magnetism), which helps her fight with her weapons (especially when throwing her shield) and subtly influence the moves of her opponents. 

h4. Physical Characteristics 

Pyrrha has [[green eyes]] and [[long_hair|long]] [[red hair]] tied in a [[ponytail]]. 

She stands 6 feet tall when wearing her usual heels. 

h4. Attire 

Pyrrha usually wears a metal headpiece (a [[circlet]] or [[forehead protector]]) around her head. Two small emeralds hang from the metal band on delicate chain loops near her ears. 

Her combat attire includes a bronze [[gorget]] around her neck, [[black_gloves|black]] (or very dark red/brown) [[elbow gloves]], a bronze metal [[armlet]] on her upper left arm, a bronze metal [[vambraces|vambrace]] secured with black cross-laces on her lower left arm (to which her shield attaches), a brown leather or dark bronze [[breastplate]] which resembles a [[corset]] secured with black cross-laces in the back, a red [[sarong]] over a dark red or [[black_skirt|black]] [[miniskirt]] (with possibly another pair of black shorts underneath), a [[buckle|buckled]] [[belt]] with circular metal plate bearing her emblem on the right and two [[belt_pouch|belt pouches]] hanging off the back, bronze metal [[leg armor]] ([[greaves]]) reaching up to mid-thigh (possibly [[zettai ryouiki]]) over dark red/brown/black thighhighs, and dark brown leather [[high heel boots]] with bronze trim. 

In school, she trades her combat outfit for the usual Beacon Academy [[school uniform|uniform]] ([[white shirt|white]] [[blouse]] with red [[neck ribbon]], brown [[blazer]], and [[plaid skirt]]), but keeps her bronze metal headpiece.

title: hajimete_no_otsukai
body:
The first errand ([i]hajimete no otsukai[/i]) refers to the first time children are sent on an errand by themselves, usually to buy groceries at the local store, and is a fairly common milestone for families in Japan. It was also the subject of a non-regular, documentary/reality television series broadcasted by [[Nippon TV]] (available on Netflix since April 2022 under the title "Old Enough!") 

Common elements in images include dragging a [[grocery bag]] with items spilling out, [[crying]], [[lost child|getting lost]] and [[carrying]] siblings. Occasionally there will be an older family member discreetly lurking nearby. Images with this tag do not need to be the [i]literal[/i] first time a character goes on an errand.

body:
The Palace of the Parliament (Romanian: [i]Palatul Parlamentului[/i]) is the current official name of the massive, multi-purpose central building (in essence a palace) built by former Romanian dictator [[Nicolae Ceausescu]]. 
However, Romanians commonly refer to it as "the People's House" ([i]Casa Poporului[/i]). 
Today, this negative heritage of the Ceausescu regime is the only tourist attraction in Bucharest due to a lot of Bucharest being cleared to make way for the colossal building in the years following the 1977 earthquake.

title: catra
body:
http://she-raandtheprincessesofpower.wikia.com/wiki/Catra
                                               
A fictional female character from the [[Masters of the Universe]] science fiction and [[fantasy]] franchise. 

She first appeared in the second cartoon series [i][b]She-Ra: Princess of Power[/b][/i] in 1985.

Catra is the second-in-command, formerly a Force Captain, in the Horde and was [[Adora (she-ra)]] 's best friend before her defection to join the Rebellion. Though she initially desired to bring Adora back into the Horde, Catra realised that Adora's absence created the opportunity for her to step out of Adora's shadow and prove her strength and cunning. Ultimately, she casts aside her former friendship in favor of her newfound strength and achievements, basking in the glory she has attained without Adora's aid.

Catra has a very messy and brownish gray hair, she has reddish black cat ears. She wears a red cat-shaped mask: with two ends representing ears and two holes representing the eyes, placed above her forehead. Catra has a dark red shirt with a layer of red breasts, she has a brown belt with the symbol of the Horde, and another belt, only thin. The feline wears a dark pink red pants with holes in the cocha and a hole in the knee and a hole in the heel and the area of the toes, where they reside dark gray claws. Catra also has a cat tail. She also has heterochromia, her right eye being light blue and her left eye being yellow.

title: lulu_(league_of_legends)
body:
A [[yordle]] Champion from The Glade near Bandle City in [[League of Legends]] usually played as a support.

Lulu has [[green eyes]], a [[long_hair|long]] [[purple_hair|purple]] hair and [[animal ears]]. She wears a [[witch hat]] and carries a [[staff]] around with her.

She is known for her whimsical nature and ability to polymorph or shrink/enlarge others. Has a [[fairy|faerie]] companion named [[Pix (league of legends)|]].

Full title: [b]Lulu, the Fae Sorceress[/b]
